mplify the testing process.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying serialization details**\\n\\nI want to check if BigInteger has a readResolve method; it seems to me that it might be final, but BigInteger itself isn't final. It does have some final components though. I wonder if subclasses can serialize appropriately. Regarding DSAParameterSpec, it looks like it's constructed with DSAParameterSpec((BigInteger) readObject) tied to tracked objects. So, maybe DSAParameterSpec does store references after all. There's definitely a lot of complexity here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6AMqsAPRT0TVFbLicwIbtWSw|fc_0e413bb866b676870169fc1ca4bc7c81a2bae30cfc03a511bf", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 838, "output": 1904, "cacheRead": 41984, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44726, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778130054991, "responseId": "resp_0e413bb866b676870169fc1c88240881a2a3b767964af735b0"}}
